Lake Tahoe Review:
Hangin with your love - 10/10 would recommend 
Views - 10/10 would 💯 recommend 
Skiing - 6/10 would kinda recommend 
Ski boots - 10/10 would NOT recommend
❄️ January 2023 ❄️

This needed its own post. This was later in the day after my ski lesson and I told Josh I wanted to try a *harder* slope… it was steeper, but still a slope for rookie skiers like me. At the beginning of this clip, you’ll watch as I convince another rookie skier that “It’s so fun and actually EASIER than the flatter slope we’d been going down.” This all before I s-l-o-w-l-y inched my way down the slope and not making it 20 feet before I fall right on my butt… shout out to Josh for his patience in this recording. He got all set up, proud of his girlfriend, my BIGGEST cheerleader… only to be disappointed 😂 until next time Tahoe!

That one time I played Ensign Vesco on the USS Titan 🖖🏽 for Star Trek: Picard! I shot this in Nov of 2021 and I’m SO excited to finally be able to share this! I was so impressed with the set, the crew, everything ran like a dream! Thanks to my incredible agent Julie and team for all the hard work (always) and shoutout to Liz Dean Casting such amazing opportunity! @lizdeancasting
It’s been raining a lot in LA … and I think I speak for everyone when I say … woof, enough already…
Our first selfie - to the day - 3 years ago… right as the world was having a meltdown, I met you. “Have I known you 20 seconds or 20 years?” Happy anniversary, love ❤️

We had such an amazing weekend with our framily in spite of Josh taking a nasty fall. It’s so so hard to watch a loved one in so much pain. I felt helpless and just wanted to make him feel better. Thanks to everyone who reached out to send positive vibes to Josh - your positivity and love really meant a lot to us. 

Josh is on the mend and finally happily drinking beer and eating all the foods. ❤️

It was so much fun working on the set of S.W.A.T @swatcbs with my co-stars and very talented director Liz @scriptclay - I even got to meet some talented writers 😏 @vikastubbs 😉 Shout out to Wendy Weidman Casting and team, my amazing reps - Julie & Evan at SHG and @brillianttalent for another great experience ❤️ Catch my episode “Genesis” now on Paramount+!

Happy 2 Year Rosie-versary to us! Two years of travel, walks, beach days, treats, cuddles, sniffing, restaurants, & helping me audition, & so much more … there are days where I think to call and speak to Rosie - on the phone. I’m going to invent a way because I think we could all benefit from hearing dogs speak.
💜love on the weekend💜
Protesting because Mom and dad got a dirty water (coffee) and didn’t get me a pup cup…

Catch your girl on “Platonic” now streaming on @appletv! The show is hilarious! Thanks to all my friends who texted, DM’d, called me to let me know I’m on tv! I honestly thought I’d be unrecognizable with my hair like that 😂

As always, thanks team @brillianttalent, S&HG, and the team at McCarthy/Abellera Casting for a great booking 🙏🏽❤️ @nicoleabhallman

Fun fact: Seth had no idea we were going to sing happy birthday for this scene 😂 he was very surprised 

And if it’s your birthday, Happy Birthday Daddio! 😏😉
☀️ Texas Sun ☀️
Happy birthday, my love! As is evident, you light up every room you’re in with your infectious energy. You also crazy 😜 I love you so much. Hope it’s a fun one 🫶🏽
A rare sighting of DJ Bobby Jangles…. 😉
Birthday celebrations continue 🙇🏽‍♀️

My first Christmas wedding- my sister and Marco - and it was just perfect! I just lauv it. The most beautiful wedding day for my sister and my (new) brother! Congratulations, you guys! I love you so much!

It’s our sweet girl’s 5th birthday today! Today she got a Mariah Carey robe, a turkey leg toy, and an In-N-Out burger (patty) ☺️ 

She’s the best travel buddy, cuddle bug, and the most mischievous little nacho gazpacho chicken nugget and I cannot imagine our lives without her 🥰 

Happy Birthday Rosie!

Finally able to post this - 2023 was one for the books. Worth all the planes, trains, automobiles, family, friends, laughs, tears, delays, dinners, brunches, lunches, swims, slopes, broken bones, broken hearts, hugs and kisses. Made new friends, lost some old ones, welcomed a few into the world, celebrated trips around the sun, and shared in some epic weddings… oh and dancing - there was SO much dancing ☺️ grateful for it all. To a successful year ahead 🫶🏽
